title: The Bachelor's Laura Byrne reveals she suffered complications giving birth to daughter Marlie-Mae
text:
She gave birth to daughter Marlie-Mae in June.

And Laura Byrne has revealed to this week's Stellar magazine that she suffered a complicated delivery with the tot, who was in a posterior position.

The 33-year-old told the magazine: 'They didn't realise it right away, either. She was stuck; they needed to get her out immediately.

'They needed to get her out immediately': The Bachelor's Laura Byrne (right) reveals she suffered complications giving birth to daughter Marlie-Mae (pictured) as she poses for this week's Stellar with fiancé Matty Johnson (right)

'So there were complications and it wasn't the easiest of births. But I was just so happy that she was out and in the world that my memory of it is not traumatic.'

Laura was induced, explaining: 'And then I was in labour and I didn't get a break. It was just a constant contraction. So after about an hour I was like, f**k this. Give me all the drugs'.

Fiancé Matty Johnson says he has taken to fatherhood like a duck to water.

In the photo shoot accompanying the magazine, the new parents look stunning as they pose with their little girl.

One photo sees Laura reclining beside Matty on a rug, in a slinky gold silk gown, as they hold their baby.

One more gorgeous photograph, Laura wears a checked cotton dress, holding Marlie-Mae close as Matty cuddles against his future wife.

Yet another beautiful frame shows Matty, wearing a white cotton shirt, holding his look-alike-daughter in the backyard.
